gurmukhi: srb sqRu Awvq By ijqy ] sB kwit dIn dRugw iqqy ]
transliteration: Sarab Satr(u) Aavat Bhe Jite|| Sabh Kaattee Doon Drougad Tite||
translation: All the blows being struck by the weapons have been annulled by the goddess Durga.

gurmukhi: Air Aaur jyiqk fwrIAM ] qyaU kwit BUim auqwirAM ]59]215]
transliteration: Ar(i) Aur Jetik Ddarooan|| Taaoo Kaattee Bhoom(i) Outaarian||59||215||
translation: Beside these all other blows, that are being struck, are being annulled and the weapons are thrown on the ground by the goddess.59.215.

gurmukhi: sr Awp kwlI CMfIAM ] srbwsqR sqRu ibhMfIAM ]
transliteration: Sar Aap Kaaloo Chhandooan|| Sarabaastra Satr(u Bihandooan||
translation: Kali herself made use of her weapons and made all the weapons of the demons ineffective.

gurmukhi: ssqR hIn jbY inhwrXo ] jY sbd dyvn aucwrXo ]60]216]
transliteration: Sastra Hoon Jabai Nihdaryo|| Jai Sabad Devan Ouchdaryo||60||216||
translation: When the gods saw (Sumbh) without weapons, they began to hail the goddess.60.216.

gurmukhi: niB m`iD bwjn bwj hIN ] Aivloik dyvw gwj hIN ]
transliteration: Nabh(i) Maddh(i) Baajan Baaj Hoon|| Avilok(i) Devaa Gadj Hoon||
translation: The musical instruments were played in the firmament and no0w the gods also began to raor.

gurmukhi: liK dyv bwrM bwr hIN ] jY sbd srb pukwr hIN ]61]217]
transliteration: Lakh(i) Dev Baaran Baar Hoon|| Jai Sabad Sarab Poukaar Hoon||61||217||
translation: The gods began to view repeatedly and raise shouts of victory.61.217.

gurmukhi: rx kop kwl krwlIXM ] K`t AMg pwx auCwlIXM ]
transliteration: Ran Kop Kaal Karaalooyan|| Khatt An Paan Oucdhaalooyan||
translation: Now in great rage in the battlefield, the dreadful Kali raised six hands of her arms powerfully;

gurmukhi: isr suMB h`Q duCMfIXM ] iek cot dust ibhMfIXM ]62]218]
transliteration: Sir Sounbh Hatth Douchhandooyan|| Ik Chot Doust Bihandooyan||62||218||
translation: And struck them on the head of Sumbh and with one blow she destroyed the tyrant.62.218.

gurmukhi: ijm suMBwsur ko hnw AiDk kop kY kwl ]
transliteration: Jim Sounbhaasur Ko Hanaa Adhik Kop Kai Kaal||
translation: The manner in which, with extreme fury, Kali destroyed the demon-king Sumbh;

gurmukhi: iqEN swDn ky sqRu sB cwbq jwNh krwl ]63]219]
transliteration: Tion Saadhan Ke Satr(u) Sabh Chaabat Jaanh Karaal||63||219||
translation: All the enemies of the saints are destroyed in the same manner.63.219.

gurmukhi: ieiq sRI bicqR nwtky cMfI cirqRy suMB bDh Kstmo iDAwie sMpUrx msqu suB msqu ]6]
transliteration: It(i) Sroo Bachita Naatake Channdoo Chartre Sounbh Badhah Khastamo Dhiaae Sanpooran Mast(u) Soubh Mast(u)||6||
translation: Here ends the Sixth Chapter entitled ‘The Killing of Sumbh’ of Chandi Charitra in BACHITTAR NATAK.6.
